"squatting, tearing out their hair and beard. For I’m living at home with my "
"children, using sandalwood imported from Kāsi, wearing garlands, perfumes, "
"and makeup, and accepting gold and money. Yet I’ll have exactly the same "
"destiny in the next life as this teacher."

msgctxt "mn76:11.10"
msgid ""
"Sohaṃ kiṃ jānanto kiṃ passanto imasmiṃ satthari brahmacariyaṃ carissāmi?"
msgstr ""
