"na vaseyya, vasanto ca nārādheyya ñāyaṃ dhammaṃ kusalan”ti."
msgstr ""
"These are the four ways that negate the spiritual life that have been "
"explained by the Blessed One, who knows and sees, the perfected one, the "
"fully awakened Buddha. A sensible person would, to the best of their "
"ability, not practice such spiritual paths, and if they did practice them, "
"they wouldn’t succeed in the procedure of the skillful teaching.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya20"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc15"></a>
msgctxt "mn76:20.1"
msgid "“Acchariyaṃ, bho ānanda, abbhutaṃ, bho ānanda."
msgstr "“It’s incredible, Master Ānanda, it’s amazing,"

msgctxt "mn76:20.2"
msgid ""
"Yāvañcidaṃ tena bhagavatā jānatā passatā arahatā sammāsambuddhena cattāro "
"abrahmacariyavāsāva samānā ‘abrahmacariyavāsā’ti akkhātā yattha viññū puriso "
"sasakkaṃ brahmacariyaṃ na vaseyya, vasanto ca nārādheyya ñāyaṃ dhammaṃ "
"kusalanti."
msgstr ""
"how these four ways that negate the spiritual life have been explained by "
"the Buddha."

msgctxt "mn76:20.3"
msgid ""
"Katamāni pana tāni, bho ānanda, tena bhagavatā jānatā passatā arahatā "
"sammāsambuddhena cattāri anassāsikāni brahmacariyāni akkhātāni yattha viññū "
"puriso sasakkaṃ brahmacariyaṃ na vaseyya, vasanto ca nārādheyya ñāyaṃ "
"dhammaṃ kusalan”ti?"
msgstr ""
"But Master Ānanda, what are the four kinds of unreliable spiritual life?”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya21"></a>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi1.520"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc16"></a>
msgctxt "mn76:21.1"
msgid ""
"“Idha, sandaka, ekacco satthā sabbaññū sabbadassāvī aparisesaṃ ñāṇadassanaṃ "
"paṭijānāti:"
msgstr ""
"“Sandaka, take a certain teacher who claims to be all-knowing and all-"
"seeing, to know and see everything without exception, thus:"

msgctxt "mn76:21.2"
msgid ""
"‘carato ca me tiṭṭhato ca suttassa ca jāgarassa ca satataṃ samitaṃ "
"ñāṇadassanaṃ paccupaṭṭhitan’ti."
msgstr ""
"‘Knowledge and vision are constantly and continually present to me, while "
"walking, standing, sleeping, and waking.’"

msgctxt "mn76:21.3"
msgid ""
"So suññampi agāraṃ pavisati, piṇḍampi na labhati, kukkuropi ḍaṃsati, "
"caṇḍenapi hatthinā samāgacchati, caṇḍenapi assena samāgacchati, caṇḍenapi "
"goṇena samāgacchati, itthiyāpi purisassapi nāmampi gottampi pucchati, "
"gāmassapi nigamassapi nāmampi maggampi pucchati."
msgstr ""
"He enters an empty house; he gets no alms-food; a dog bites him; he "
"encounters a wild elephant, a wild horse, and a wild cow; he asks the name "
"and clan of a woman or man; he asks the name and path to a village or town."

#. VAR: tenamhi → tena (mr) | tenāsiṃ (?)
msgctxt "mn76:21.4"
msgid ""
"So ‘kimidan’ti puṭṭho samāno ‘suññaṃ me agāraṃ pavisitabbaṃ ahosi’, tena "
"pāvisiṃ; ‘piṇḍampi aladdhabbaṃ ahosi’, tena nālatthaṃ; ‘kukkurena "
"ḍaṃsitabbaṃ ahosi’, tenamhi daṭṭho; ‘caṇḍena hatthinā samāgantabbaṃ ahosi’, "
"tena samāgamiṃ; ‘caṇḍena assena samāgantabbaṃ ahosi’, tena samāgamiṃ; ‘"
"caṇḍena goṇena samāgantabbaṃ ahosi’, tena samāgamiṃ; ‘itthiyāpi purisassapi "
"nāmampi gottampi pucchitabbaṃ ahosi’, tena pucchiṃ; ‘gāmassapi nigamassapi "
"nāmampi maggampi pucchitabbaṃ ahosi’, tena pucchinti."
msgstr ""
"When asked, ‘Why is this?’ he answers: ‘I had to enter an empty house, that’"
"s why I entered it. I had to get no alms-food, that’s why I got none. I had "
"to get bitten by a dog, that’s why I was bitten. I had to encounter a wild "
"elephant, a wild horse, and a wild cow, that’s why I encountered them. I had "
"to ask the name and clan of a woman or man, that’s why I asked. I had to ask "
"the name and path to a village or town, that’s why I asked.’"

#. <a class="nya" id="nya22"></a>
msgctxt "mn76:22.1"
msgid "Tatra, sandaka, viññū puriso iti paṭisañcikkhati:"
msgstr "A sensible person reflects on this matter in this way:"

msgctxt "mn76:22.2"
msgid ""
"‘ayaṃ kho bhavaṃ satthā sabbaññū sabbadassāvī aparisesaṃ ñāṇadassanaṃ "
"paṭijānāti … pe … ‘gāmassapi nigamassapi nāmampi maggampi pucchitabbaṃ "
"ahosi, tena pucchin’ti."
msgstr "‘This teacher makes such a claim, but he answers in such a way."

msgctxt "mn76:22.3"
msgid "So ‘anassāsikaṃ idaṃ brahmacariyan’ti—"
msgstr "This spiritual life is unreliable.’"

msgctxt "mn76:22.4"
msgid "iti viditvā tasmā brahmacariyā nibbijja pakkamati."
msgstr "Realizing this, they leave disappointed."

#. <a class="nya" id="nya23"></a>
msgctxt "mn76:23.1"
msgid ""
"Idaṃ kho, sandaka, tena bhagavatā jānatā passatā arahatā sammāsambuddhena "
"paṭhamaṃ anassāsikaṃ brahmacariyaṃ akkhātaṃ yattha viññū puriso sasakkaṃ "
"brahmacariyaṃ na vaseyya, vasanto ca nārādheyya ñāyaṃ dhammaṃ kusalaṃ."
msgstr "This is the first kind of unreliable spiritual life."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya24"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc17"></a>
msgctxt "mn76:24.1"
msgid "Puna caparaṃ, sandaka, idhekacco satthā anussaviko hoti anussavasacco."
msgstr ""
"Furthermore, take another teacher who is an oral transmitter, who takes oral "
"transmission to be the truth."

msgctxt "mn76:24.2"
msgid "So anussavena itihitihaparamparāya piṭakasampadāya dhammaṃ deseti."
msgstr ""
"He teaches by oral transmission, by the lineage of testament, by canonical "
"authority."

msgctxt "mn76:24.3"
msgid ""
"Anussavikassa kho pana, sandaka, satthuno anussavasaccassa sussutampi hoti "
"dussutampi hoti tathāpi hoti aññathāpi hoti."
msgstr ""
"But when a teacher takes oral transmission to be the truth, some of that is "
"well learned, some poorly learned, some true, and some otherwise."

#. <a class="nya" id="nya25"></a>
msgctxt "mn76:25.1"
msgid "Tatra, sandaka, viññū puriso iti paṭisañcikkhati:"
msgstr "A sensible person reflects on this matter in this way:"

msgctxt "mn76:25.2"
msgid ""
"‘ayaṃ kho bhavaṃ satthā anussaviko anussavasacco so anussavena "
"itihitihaparamparāya piṭakasampadāya dhammaṃ deseti."
msgstr ""
"‘This teacher takes oral transmission to be the truth. He teaches by oral "
"transmission, by the lineage of testament, by canonical authority."

msgctxt "mn76:25.3"
msgid ""
"Anussavikassa kho pana satthuno anussavasaccassa sussutampi hoti dussutampi "
"hoti tathāpi hoti aññathāpi hoti’."
msgstr ""
"But when a teacher takes oral transmission to be the truth, some of that is "
"well learned, some poorly learned, some true, and some otherwise."

msgctxt "mn76:25.4"
msgid "So ‘anassāsikaṃ idaṃ brahmacariyan’ti—"
msgstr "This spiritual life is unreliable.’"

msgctxt "mn76:25.5"
msgid "iti viditvā tasmā brahmacariyā nibbijja pakkamati."
msgstr "Realizing this, they leave disappointed."

#. <a class="nya" id="nya26"></a>
msgctxt "mn76:26.1"
msgid ""
"Idaṃ kho, sandaka, tena bhagavatā jānatā passatā arahatā sammāsambuddhena "
"dutiyaṃ anassāsikaṃ brahmacariyaṃ akkhātaṃ yattha viññū puriso sasakkaṃ "
"brahmacariyaṃ na vaseyya, vasanto ca nārādheyya ñāyaṃ dhammaṃ kusalaṃ."
msgstr "This is the second kind of unreliable spiritual life."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya27"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc18"></a>
msgctxt "mn76:27.1"
msgid "Puna caparaṃ, sandaka, idhekacco satthā takkī hoti vīmaṃsī."
msgstr "Furthermore, take another teacher who relies on logic and inquiry."

msgctxt "mn76:27.2"
msgid "So takkapariyāhataṃ vīmaṃsānucaritaṃ sayampaṭibhānaṃ dhammaṃ deseti."
msgstr ""
"He teaches what he has worked out by logic, following a line of inquiry, "
"expressing his own perspective."

msgctxt "mn76:27.3"
msgid ""
"Takkissa kho pana, sandaka, satthuno vīmaṃsissa sutakkitampi hoti "
"duttakkitampi hoti tathāpi hoti aññathāpi hoti."
msgstr ""
"But when a teacher relies on logic and inquiry, some of that is well "
"reasoned, some poorly reasoned, some true, and some otherwise."

#. <a class="nya" id="nya28"></a>
msgctxt "mn76:28.1"
msgid "Tatra, sandaka, viññū puriso iti paṭisañcikkhati:"
msgstr "A sensible person reflects on this matter in this way:"

msgctxt "mn76:28.2"
msgid "‘ayaṃ kho bhavaṃ satthā takkī vīmaṃsī."
msgstr "‘This teacher relies on logic and inquiry."

msgctxt "mn76:28.3"
msgid "So takkapariyāhataṃ vīmaṃsānucaritaṃ sayampaṭibhānaṃ dhammaṃ deseti."
msgstr ""
"He teaches what he has worked out by logic, following a line of inquiry, "
"expressing his own perspective."

msgctxt "mn76:28.4"
msgid ""
"Takkissa kho pana satthuno vīmaṃsissa sutakkitampi hoti duttakkitampi hoti "
"tathāpi hoti aññathāpi hoti’."
msgstr ""
"But when a teacher relies on logic and inquiry, some of that is well "
"reasoned, some poorly reasoned, some true, and some otherwise."

msgctxt "mn76:28.5"
msgid "So ‘anassāsikaṃ idaṃ brahmacariyan’ti—"
msgstr "This spiritual life is unreliable.’"

msgctxt "mn76:28.6"
msgid "iti viditvā tasmā brahmacariyā nibbijja pakkamati."
msgstr "Realizing this, they leave disappointed."

#. <a class="nya" id="nya29"></a>
msgctxt "mn76:29.1"
msgid ""
"Idaṃ kho, sandaka, tena bhagavatā jānatā passatā arahatā sammāsambuddhena "
"tatiyaṃ anassāsikaṃ brahmacariyaṃ akkhātaṃ yattha viññū puriso sasakkaṃ "
"brahmacariyaṃ na vaseyya, vasanto ca nārādheyya ñāyaṃ dhammaṃ kusalaṃ."
msgstr "This is the third kind of unreliable spiritual life."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya30"></a>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi1.521"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc19"></a>
msgctxt "mn76:30.1"
msgid "Puna caparaṃ, sandaka, idhekacco satthā mando hoti momūho."
msgstr "Furthermore, take another teacher who is dull and stupid."

# I don’t find the commentarial explanation of amarā as “fish” to be plausible. The word appears nowhere else, and feels to me like a back-formation. To me it smells, well, fishy. DA 21 has 異問異答, “other question other answer”, where 異 evidently stands for añña or similar. In the other available translation on SC at T 21, I can’t determine the exact term, but in any case, it doesn’t seem to contain any reference to eels or fish. I can’t access the other parallels ATM. Using “eel-wriggling” is over-determining a dubious metaphor, and it is better to translate according to the sense.
#. VAR: tattha tattha → tathā tathā (bj, s1-3, km, pts1)
msgctxt "mn76:30.2"
msgid ""
"So mandattā momūhattā tattha tattha pañhaṃ puṭṭho samāno vācāvikkhepaṃ "
"āpajjati amarāvikkhepaṃ:"
msgstr ""
"Because of that, whenever he’s asked a question, he resorts to evasiveness "
"and equivocation:"

#. VAR: aññathātipi → aññathāpi (bj, pts1)
#. VAR: tathātipi → tathāpi (bj, pts1)
#. VAR: evantipi → evampi (bj, pts1)
msgctxt "mn76:30.3"
msgid ""
"‘evantipi me no, tathātipi me no, aññathātipi me no, notipi me no, no notipi "
"me no’ti."
msgstr ""
"‘I don’t say it’s like this. I don’t say it’s like that. I don’t say it’s "
"otherwise. I don’t say it’s not so. And I don’t deny it’s not so.’"

#. <a class="nya" id="nya31"></a>
msgctxt "mn76:31.1"
msgid "Tatra, sandaka, viññū puriso iti paṭisañcikkhati:"
msgstr "A sensible person reflects on this matter in this way:"

msgctxt "mn76:31.2"
msgid "‘ayaṃ kho bhavaṃ satthā mando momūho."
msgstr "‘This teacher is dull and stupid."

msgctxt "mn76:31.3"
msgid ""
"So mandattā momūhattā tattha tattha pañhaṃ puṭṭho samāno vācāvikkhepaṃ "
"āpajjati amarāvikkhepaṃ—"
msgstr ""
"Because of that, whenever he’s asked a question, he resorts to evasiveness "
"and equivocation:"

msgctxt "mn76:31.4"
msgid ""
"evantipi me no, tathātipi me no, aññathātipi me no, notipi me no, no notipi "
"me no’ti."
msgstr ""
"“I don’t say it’s like this. I don’t say it’s like that. I don’t say it’s "
"otherwise. I don’t say it’s not so. And I don’t deny it’s not so.”"

msgctxt "mn76:31.5"
msgid "So ‘anassāsikaṃ idaṃ brahmacariyan’ti—"
msgstr "This spiritual life is unreliable.’"

msgctxt "mn76:31.6"
msgid "iti viditvā tasmā brahmacariyā nibbijja pakkamati."
msgstr "Realizing this, they leave disappointed."

#. <a class="nya" id="nya32"></a>
msgctxt "mn76:32.1"
msgid ""
"Idaṃ kho, sandaka, tena bhagavatā jānatā passatā arahatā sammāsambuddhena "
"catutthaṃ anassāsikaṃ brahmacariyaṃ akkhātaṃ yattha viññū puriso sasakkaṃ "
"brahmacariyaṃ na vaseyya, vasanto ca nārādheyya ñāyaṃ dhammaṃ kusalaṃ."
msgstr "This is the fourth kind of unreliable spiritual life."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya33"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc20"></a>
#. VAR: tāni → idaṃ padaṃ bj, s1-3, pts1 potthakesu
msgctxt "mn76:33.1"
msgid ""
"Imāni kho tāni, sandaka, tena bhagavatā jānatā passatā arahatā "
"sammāsambuddhena cattāri anassāsikāni brahmacariyāni akkhātāni yattha viññū "
"puriso sasakkaṃ brahmacariyaṃ na vaseyya, vasanto ca nārādheyya ñāyaṃ "
"dhammaṃ kusalan”ti."
msgstr ""
"These are the four kinds of unreliable spiritual life that have been "
"explained by the Blessed One, who knows and sees, the perfected one, the "
"fully awakened Buddha. A sensible person would, to the best of their "
"ability, not practice such spiritual paths, and if they did practice them, "
"they wouldn’t complete the procedure of the skillful teaching.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya34"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc21"></a>
msgctxt "mn76:34.1"
msgid "“Acchariyaṃ, bho ānanda, abbhutaṃ, bho ānanda."
msgstr "“It’s incredible, Master Ānanda, it’s amazing,"

msgctxt "mn76:34.2"
msgid ""
"Yāvañcidaṃ tena bhagavatā jānatā passatā arahatā sammāsambuddhena cattāri "
"anassāsikāneva brahmacariyāni anassāsikāni brahmacariyānīti akkhātāni yattha "
"viññū puriso sasakkaṃ brahmacariyaṃ na vaseyya, vasanto ca nārādheyya ñāyaṃ "
"dhammaṃ kusalaṃ."
msgstr ""
"how these four kinds of unreliable spiritual life have been explained by the "
"Buddha."

msgctxt "mn76:34.3"
msgid ""
"So pana, bho ānanda, satthā kiṃ vādī kiṃ akkhāyī yattha viññū puriso "
"sasakkaṃ brahmacariyaṃ vaseyya, vasanto ca ārādheyya ñāyaṃ dhammaṃ "
"kusalan”ti."
msgstr ""
"But, Master Ānanda, what would a teacher say and explain so that a sensible "
"person would, to the best of their ability, practice such a spiritual path, "
"and once practicing it, they would complete the procedure of the skillful "
"teaching?”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya35-42"></a>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi1.522"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc22"></a>
msgctxt "mn76:35-42.1"
msgid ""
"“Idha, sandaka, tathāgato loke uppajjati arahaṃ sammāsambuddho "
"vijjācaraṇasampanno sugato lokavidū anuttaro purisadammasārathi satthā "
"devamanussānaṃ buddho bhagavā … pe …"
msgstr ""
"“Sandaka, it’s when a Realized One arises in the world, perfected, a fully "
"awakened Buddha, accomplished in knowledge and conduct, holy, knower of the "
"world, supreme guide for those who wish to train, teacher of gods and "
"humans, awakened, blessed. …"

msgctxt "mn76:35-42.2"
msgid "so ime pañca nīvaraṇe pahāya cetaso upakkilese paññāya dubbalīkaraṇe "
msgstr ""
"He gives up these five hindrances, corruptions of the heart that weaken "
"wisdom. "

msgctxt "mn76:35-42.3"
msgid ""
"vivicceva kāmehi vivicca akusalehi dhammehi savitakkaṃ savicāraṃ vivekajaṃ "
"pītisukhaṃ paṭhamaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja viharati."
msgstr ""
"Then, quite secluded from sensual pleasures, secluded from unskillful "
"qualities, he enters and remains in the first absorption, which has the "
"rapture and bliss born of seclusion, while placing the mind and keeping it "
"connected."

#. VAR: Yasmiṃ kho → yasmiṃ kho pana (s1-3, km, mr)
msgctxt "mn76:35-42.4"
msgid ""
"Yasmiṃ kho, sandaka, satthari sāvako evarūpaṃ uḷāravisesaṃ adhigacchati "
"tattha viññū puriso sasakkaṃ brahmacariyaṃ vaseyya, vasanto ca ārādheyya "
"ñāyaṃ dhammaṃ kusalaṃ."
msgstr ""
"A sensible person would, to the best of their ability live the spiritual "
"life under a teacher who achieves such a high distinction, and, once "
"practicing it, they would complete the procedure of the skillful teaching."

# Bhikkhu here seems improbable. yet it is attested in the Mss, so I include it. BB omits.
#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya43"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc23"></a>
msgctxt "mn76:43.1"
msgid ""
"Puna caparaṃ, sandaka, bhikkhu vitakkavicārānaṃ vūpasamā … pe … dutiyaṃ "
"jhānaṃ upasampajja viharati."
msgstr ""
"Furthermore, as the placing of the mind and keeping it connected are "
"stilled, a mendicant … enters and remains in the second absorption …"

msgctxt "mn76:43.2"
msgid ""
"Yasmiṃ kho, sandaka, satthari sāvako evarūpaṃ uḷāravisesaṃ adhigacchati "
"tattha viññū puriso sasakkaṃ brahmacariyaṃ vaseyya, vasanto ca ārādheyya "
"ñāyaṃ dhammaṃ kusalaṃ."
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya44-45"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc24"></a>
msgctxt "mn76:44-45.1"
msgid ""
"Puna caparaṃ, sandaka, bhikkhu pītiyā ca virāgā upekkhako ca viharati … pe … "
"tatiyaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja viharati."
msgstr "third absorption …"

msgctxt "mn76:44-45.2"
msgid ""
"Yasmiṃ kho, sandaka, satthari sāvako evarūpaṃ uḷāravisesaṃ adhigacchati "
"tattha viññū puriso sasakkaṃ brahmacariyaṃ vaseyya, vasanto ca ārādheyya "
"ñāyaṃ dhammaṃ kusalaṃ."
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya46"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc25"></a>
msgctxt "mn76:46.1"
msgid ""
"Puna caparaṃ, sandaka, bhikkhu sukhassa ca pahānā … pe … catutthaṃ jhānaṃ "
"upasampajja viharati."
msgstr "fourth absorption."

msgctxt "mn76:46.2"
msgid ""
"Yasmiṃ kho, sandaka, satthari sāvako evarūpaṃ uḷāravisesaṃ adhigacchati "
"tattha viññū puriso sasakkaṃ brahmacariyaṃ vaseyya, vasanto ca ārādheyya "
"ñāyaṃ dhammaṃ kusalaṃ."
msgstr ""
"A sensible person would, to the best of their ability live the spiritual "
"life under a teacher who achieves such a high distinction, and, once "
"practicing it, they would complete the procedure of the skillful teaching."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya47"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc26"></a>
msgctxt "mn76:47.1"
msgid ""
"So evaṃ samāhite citte parisuddhe pariyodāte anaṅgaṇe vigatūpakkilese "
"mudubhūte kammaniye ṭhite āneñjappatte pubbenivāsānussatiñāṇāya cittaṃ "
"abhininnāmeti."
msgstr ""
"When their mind has become immersed in samādhi like this—purified, bright, "
"flawless, rid of imperfections, pliable, workable, steady, and imperturbable—"
"they extend it toward recollection of past lives."

msgctxt "mn76:47.2"
msgid ""
"So anekavihitaṃ pubbenivāsaṃ anussarati, seyyathidaṃ—ekampi jātiṃ dvepi "
"jātiyo … pe … iti sākāraṃ sauddesaṃ anekavihitaṃ pubbenivāsaṃ anussarati."
msgstr ""
"They recollect many kinds of past lives. That is: one, two, three, four, "
"five, ten, twenty, thirty, forty, fifty, a hundred, a thousand, a hundred "
"thousand rebirths; many eons of the world contracting, many eons of the "
"world evolving, many eons of the world contracting and evolving. … They "
"recollect their many kinds of past lives, with features and details."

msgctxt "mn76:47.3"
msgid ""
"Yasmiṃ kho, sandaka, satthari sāvako evarūpaṃ uḷāravisesaṃ adhigacchati "
"tattha viññū puriso sasakkaṃ brahmacariyaṃ vaseyya, vasanto ca ārādheyya "
"ñāyaṃ dhammaṃ kusalaṃ."
msgstr ""
"A sensible person would, to the best of their ability live the spiritual "
"life under a teacher who achieves such a high distinction, and, once "
"practicing it, they would complete the procedure of the skillful teaching."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya48"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc27"></a>
msgctxt "mn76:48.1"
msgid ""
"So evaṃ samāhite citte parisuddhe pariyodāte anaṅgaṇe vigatūpakkilese "
"mudubhūte kammaniye ṭhite āneñjappatte sattānaṃ cutūpapātañāṇāya cittaṃ "
"abhininnāmeti."
msgstr ""
"When their mind has become immersed in samādhi like this—purified, bright, "
"flawless, rid of imperfections, pliable, workable, steady, and imperturbable—"
"they extend it toward knowledge of the death and rebirth of sentient beings."

msgctxt "mn76:48.2"
msgid ""
"So dibbena cakkhunā visuddhena atikkantamānusakena satte passati cavamāne "
"upapajjamāne hīne paṇīte suvaṇṇe dubbaṇṇe sugate duggate … pe … "
"yathākammūpage satte pajānāti."
msgstr ""
"With clairvoyance that is purified and superhuman, they see sentient beings "
"passing away and being reborn—inferior and superior, beautiful and ugly, in "
"a good place or a bad place. … They understand how sentient beings are "
"reborn according to their deeds."

msgctxt "mn76:48.3"
msgid ""
"Yasmiṃ kho, sandaka, satthari sāvako evarūpaṃ uḷāravisesaṃ adhigacchati "
"tattha viññū puriso sasakkaṃ brahmacariyaṃ vaseyya, vasanto ca ārādheyya "
"ñāyaṃ dhammaṃ kusalaṃ."
msgstr ""
"A sensible person would, to the best of their ability live the spiritual "
"life under a teacher who achieves such a high distinction, and, once "
"practicing it, they would complete the procedure of the skillful teaching."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya49"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc28"></a>
msgctxt "mn76:49.1"
msgid ""
"So evaṃ samāhite citte parisuddhe pariyodāte anaṅgaṇe vigatūpakkilese "
"mudubhūte kammaniye ṭhite āneñjappatte āsavānaṃ khayañāṇāya cittaṃ "
"abhininnāmeti."
msgstr ""
"When their mind has become immersed in samādhi like this—purified, bright, "
"flawless, rid of imperfections, pliable, workable, steady, and imperturbable—"
"they extend it toward knowledge of the ending of defilements."

msgctxt "mn76:49.2"
msgid ""
"So ‘idaṃ dukkhan’ti yathābhūtaṃ pajānāti, ‘ayaṃ dukkhasamudayo’ti "
"yathābhūtaṃ pajānāti, ‘ayaṃ dukkhanirodho’ti yathābhūtaṃ pajānāti, ‘ayaṃ "
"dukkhanirodhagāminī paṭipadā’ti yathābhūtaṃ pajānāti;"
msgstr ""
"They truly understand: ‘This is suffering’ … ‘This is the origin of "
"suffering’ … ‘This is the cessation of suffering’ … ‘This is the practice "
"that leads to the cessation of suffering’."

msgctxt "mn76:49.3"
msgid ""
"‘ime āsavā’ti yathābhūtaṃ pajānāti, ‘ayaṃ āsavasamudayo’ti yathābhūtaṃ "
"pajānāti, ‘ayaṃ āsavanirodho’ti yathābhūtaṃ pajānāti, ‘ayaṃ "
"āsavanirodhagāminī paṭipadā’ti yathābhūtaṃ pajānāti."
msgstr ""
"They truly understand: ‘These are defilements’ … ‘This is the origin of "
"defilements’ … ‘This is the cessation of defilements’ … ‘This is the "
"practice that leads to the cessation of defilements’."

#. <a class="nya" id="nya50"></a>
msgctxt "mn76:50.1"
msgid ""
"Tassa evaṃ jānato evaṃ passato kāmāsavāpi cittaṃ vimuccati, bhavāsavāpi "
"cittaṃ vimuccati, avijjāsavāpi cittaṃ vimuccati."
msgstr ""
"Knowing and seeing like this, their mind is freed from the defilements of "
"sensuality, desire to be reborn, and ignorance."

msgctxt "mn76:50.2"
msgid "Vimuttasmiṃ vimuttamiti ñāṇaṃ hoti."
msgstr "When they’re freed, they know they’re freed."

msgctxt "mn76:50.3"
msgid ""
"‘Khīṇā jāti, vusitaṃ brahmacariyaṃ, kataṃ karaṇīyaṃ, nāparaṃ itthattāyā’ti "
"pajānāti."
msgstr ""
"They understand: ‘Rebirth is ended, the spiritual journey has been "
"completed, what had to be done has been done, there is no return to any "
"state of existence.’"

msgctxt "mn76:50.4"
msgid ""
"Yasmiṃ kho, sandaka, satthari sāvako evarūpaṃ uḷāravisesaṃ adhigacchati "
"tattha viññū puriso sasakkaṃ brahmacariyaṃ vaseyya, vasanto ca ārādheyya "
"ñāyaṃ dhammaṃ kusalan”ti."
msgstr ""
"A sensible person would, to the best of their ability live the spiritual "
"life under a teacher who achieves such a high distinction, and, once "
"practicing it, they would complete the procedure of the skillful teaching.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya51"></a>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi1.523"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc29"></a>
msgctxt "mn76:51.1"
msgid ""
"“Yo pana so, bho ānanda, bhikkhu arahaṃ khīṇāsavo vusitavā katakaraṇīyo "
"ohitabhāro anuppattasadattho parikkhīṇabhavasaṃyojano sammadaññā vimutto "
"paribhuñjeyya so kāme”ti?"
msgstr ""
"“But Master Ānanda, when a mendicant is perfected—with defilements ended, "
"who has completed the spiritual journey, done what had to be done, laid down "
"the burden, achieved their own true goal, utterly ended the fetters of "
"rebirth, and is rightly freed through enlightenment—could they still enjoy "
"sensual pleasures?”"

msgctxt "mn76:51.2"
msgid ""
"“Yo so, sandaka, bhikkhu arahaṃ khīṇāsavo vusitavā katakaraṇīyo ohitabhāro "
"anuppattasadattho parikkhīṇabhavasaṃyojano sammadaññāvimutto, abhabbo so "
"pañcaṭṭhānāni ajjhācarituṃ."
msgstr ""
"“Sandaka, a mendicant who is perfected—with defilements ended, who has "
"completed the spiritual journey, done what had to be done, laid down the "
"burden, achieved their own true goal, utterly ended the fetters of rebirth, "
"and is rightly freed through enlightenment—can’t transgress in five respects."

msgctxt "mn76:51.3"
msgid ""
"Abhabbo khīṇāsavo bhikkhu sañcicca pāṇaṃ jīvitā voropetuṃ, abhabbo khīṇāsavo "
"bhikkhu adinnaṃ theyyasaṅkhātaṃ ādātuṃ, abhabbo khīṇāsavo bhikkhu methunaṃ "
"dhammaṃ paṭisevetuṃ, abhabbo khīṇāsavo bhikkhu sampajānamusā bhāsituṃ, "
"abhabbo khīṇāsavo bhikkhu sannidhikārakaṃ kāme paribhuñjituṃ, seyyathāpi "
"pubbe agāriyabhūto."
msgstr ""
"A mendicant with defilements ended can’t deliberately take the life of a "
"living creature, take something with the intention to steal, have sex, tell "
"a deliberate lie, or store up goods for their own enjoyment like they did as "
"a lay person."

msgctxt "mn76:51.4"
msgid ""
"Yo so, sandaka, bhikkhu arahaṃ khīṇāsavo vusitavā katakaraṇīyo ohitabhāro "
"anuppattasadattho parikkhīṇabhavasaṃyojano sammadaññāvimutto, abhabbo so "
"imāni pañcaṭṭhānāni ajjhācaritun”ti."
msgstr "A mendicant who is perfected can’t transgress in these five respects.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya52"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc30"></a>
msgctxt "mn76:52.1"
msgid ""
"“Yo pana so, bho ānanda, bhikkhu arahaṃ khīṇāsavo vusitavā katakaraṇīyo "
"ohitabhāro anuppattasadattho parikkhīṇabhavasaṃyojano sammadaññāvimutto "
"tassa carato ceva tiṭṭhato ca suttassa ca jāgarassa ca satataṃ samitaṃ "
"ñāṇadassanaṃ paccupaṭṭhitaṃ:"
msgstr ""
"“But Master Ānanda, when a mendicant is perfected, would the knowledge and "
"vision that their defilements are ended be constantly and continually "
"present to them, while walking, standing, sleeping, and waking?”"

msgctxt "mn76:52.2"
msgid "‘khīṇā me āsavā’”ti?"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn76:52.3"
msgid "“Tena hi, sandaka, upamaṃ te karissāmi;"
msgstr "“Well then, Sandaka, I shall give you a simile."

msgctxt "mn76:52.4"
msgid "upamāyapidhekacce viññū purisā bhāsitassa atthaṃ ājānanti."
msgstr ""
"For by means of a simile some sensible people understand the meaning of what "
"is said."

msgctxt "mn76:52.5"
msgid "Seyyathāpi, sandaka, purisassa hatthapādā chinnā;"
msgstr "Suppose there was a person whose hands and feet had been amputated."

msgctxt "mn76:52.6"
msgid ""
"tassa carato ceva tiṭṭhato ca suttassa ca jāgarassa ca satataṃ samitaṃ "
"jānāti:"
msgstr ""
"Would they be aware that their hands and feet had been amputated constantly "
"and continually, while walking, standing, sleeping, and waking?"

msgctxt "mn76:52.7"
msgid "‘chinnā me hatthapādā’ti, udāhu paccavekkhamāno jānāti:"
msgstr "Or would they be aware of it only when they reflected on it?”"

msgctxt "mn76:52.8"
msgid "‘chinnā me hatthapādā’”ti?"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn76:52.9"
msgid "“Na kho, bho ānanda, so puriso satataṃ samitaṃ jānāti:"
msgstr "“They wouldn’t be aware of it constantly,"

msgctxt "mn76:52.10"
msgid "‘chinnā me hatthapādā’ti."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn76:52.11"
msgid "Api ca kho pana naṃ paccavekkhamāno jānāti:"
msgstr "only when they reflected on it.”"

msgctxt "mn76:52.12"
msgid "‘chinnā me hatthapādā’”ti."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn76:52.13"
msgid ""
"“Evameva kho, sandaka, yo so bhikkhu arahaṃ khīṇāsavo vusitavā katakaraṇīyo "
"ohitabhāro anuppattasadattho parikkhīṇabhavasaṃyojano sammadaññāvimutto "
"tassa carato ceva tiṭṭhato ca suttassa ca jāgarassa ca satataṃ samitaṃ "
"ñāṇadassanaṃ na paccupaṭṭhitaṃ:"
msgstr ""
"“In the same way, when a mendicant is perfected, the knowledge and vision "
"that their defilements are ended is not constantly and continually present "
"to them, while walking, standing, sleeping, and waking."

msgctxt "mn76:52.14"
msgid "‘khīṇā me āsavā’ti;"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn76:52.15"
msgid "api ca kho pana naṃ paccavekkhamāno jānāti:"
msgstr "Rather, they are aware of it only when they reflect on it.”"

msgctxt "mn76:52.16"
msgid "‘khīṇā me āsavā’”ti."
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya53"></a>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi1.524"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc31"></a>
msgctxt "mn76:53.1"
msgid "“Kīvabahukā pana, bho ānanda, imasmiṃ dhammavinaye niyyātāro”ti?"
msgstr ""
"“But Reverend Ānanda, how many emancipators are there in this teaching and "
"training?”"

msgctxt "mn76:53.2"
msgid ""
"“Na kho, sandaka, ekaṃyeva sataṃ na dve satāni na tīṇi satāni na cattāri "
"satāni na pañca satāni, atha kho bhiyyova ye imasmiṃ dhammavinaye "
"niyyātāro”ti."
msgstr ""
"“There are not just one hundred emancipators, Sandaka, or two or three or "
"four or five hundred, but many more than that in this teaching and training.”"

msgctxt "mn76:53.3"
msgid "“Acchariyaṃ, bho ānanda, abbhutaṃ, bho ānanda."
msgstr "“It’s incredible, Master Ānanda, it’s amazing!"

msgctxt "mn76:53.4"
msgid ""
"Na ca nāma sadhammokkaṃsanā bhavissati, na paradhammavambhanā, āyatane ca "
"dhammadesanā tāva bahukā ca niyyātāro paññāyissanti."
msgstr ""
"Namely, that there’s no glorifying one’s own teaching and putting down the "
"teaching of others. The Dhamma is taught in its own field, and so many "
"emancipators are recognized."

msgctxt "mn76:53.5"
msgid ""
"Ime panājīvakā puttamatāya puttā attānañceva ukkaṃsenti, pare ca vambhenti "
"tayo ceva niyyātāro paññapenti, seyyathidaṃ—"
msgstr ""
"But these <i>Ājīvakas</i>, those sons of dead sons, glorify themselves and "
"put others down. And they only recognize three emancipators:"

msgctxt "mn76:53.6"
msgid "nandaṃ vacchaṃ, kisaṃ saṅkiccaṃ, makkhaliṃ gosālan”ti."
msgstr "Nanda Vaccha, Kisa Saṅkicca, and Makkhali Gosāla.”"

#. <a class="nya" id="nya54"></a>
msgctxt "mn76:54.1"
msgid "Atha kho sandako paribbājako sakaṃ parisaṃ āmantesi:"
msgstr "Then the wanderer Sandaka addressed his own assembly:"

msgctxt "mn76:54.2"
msgid "“carantu bhonto samaṇe gotame brahmacariyavāso."
msgstr "“Go, good sirs. The spiritual life is lived under the ascetic Gotama."

msgctxt "mn76:54.3"
msgid "Na dāni sukaraṃ amhehi lābhasakkārasiloke pariccajitun”ti."
msgstr "It’s not easy for me to give up possessions, honor, or popularity now.”"

msgctxt "mn76:54.4"
msgid ""
"Iti hidaṃ sandako paribbājako sakaṃ parisaṃ uyyojesi bhagavati "
"brahmacariyeti."
msgstr ""
"And that’s how the wanderer Sandaka sent his own assembly to live the "
"spiritual life under the Buddha."

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "mn76:54.5"
msgid "Sandakasuttaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ chaṭṭhaṃ."
msgstr ""
